value.value: An insertion of the amino acid histidine between the histidine at position 773 and the valine at position 774 of the epidermal growth factor receptor protein.
An insertion of three nucleotides, cytosine-adenine-cytosine, between position 2319 and 2320 of the coding sequence of the EGFR gene.
A regimen consisting of asparaginase, cyclophosphamide, daunorubicin, prednisone, and vincristine that may be used in the treatment of acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL).
An insertion of the amino acid sequence asparagine-proline-histidine between the histidine at position 773 and the valine at position 774 of the epidermal growth factor receptor protein.
An insertion of nine nucleotides, AACCCCCAC, between position 2319 and 2320 of the coding sequence of the EGFR gene.
An insertion of the amino acid sequence proline-histidine between the histidine at position 773 and the valine at position 774 of the epidermal growth factor receptor protein.
An insertion of six nucleotides, cytosine-cytosine-cytosine-cytosine-cytosine-adenine, between position 2318 and 2319 of the coding sequence of the EGFR gene.
An insertion of six nucleotides, cytosine-cytosine-cytosine-cytosine-adenine-cytosine, between position 2319 and 2320 of the coding sequence of the EGFR gene.
An insertion of the amino acid sequence histidine-valine between the valine at position 774 and the cysteine at position 775 of the epidermal growth factor receptor protein.

An insertion of six nucleotides, cytosine-cytosine-adenine-cytosine-guanine-thymine, between position 2321 and 2322 of the coding sequence of the EGFR gene.

A complex nucleotide substitution where the deletion of guanine at position 2322 is followed by the insertion of seven nucleotides, cytosine-cytosine-adenine-cytosine-guanine-thymine-guanine, into the coding sequence of the EGFR gene.

An autosomal recessive inherited disorder caused by mutations in the SRD5A2 gene. It is characterized by deficiency of the enzyme steroid 5-alpha reductase 2 that catalyzes the conversion of testosterone to dihydrotestosterone. It results in disruption of the formation of male genitalia. Patients present with pseudohermaphroditism.

An oligosaccharide anthracycline antibiotic isolated from strains of the bacterium Streptomyces galilaeus with potential antineoplastic activity. These agents display potent antitumor properties due to their ability to intercalate into DNA and interfere with the function of both the topoisomerase I and II enzymes, thereby inhibiting DNA replication and ultimately, interfering with RNA and protein synthesis.
The protrusion of abdominal contents through a congenital or acquired defect in the abdominal wall.
Formation of blood clot in the lumen of the abdominal aorta. It may lead to severe abdominal pain and ischemic necrosis of the intestine.
The glandular stomach of the ruminant.
The actual number of subjects entered into a clinical trial.

A study design which includes a prospectively planned opportunity for modification of one or more specified aspects of the study design and/or hypotheses based on analysis of data, usually interim data.
The determination of the amount of adenovirus viral load present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of anti-activated Factor X present in a sample. This test is used to monitor low molecular weight or unfractionated heparin levels in a biological specimen.
A partial congenic mouse with background strain of C57BL/6 and 129/Sv chimera, containing a heterozygous or homozygous p53 mutation.
A benign dermal neoplasm comprising of round cells, resembling histiocytes. The tumor commonly occurs in young dogs and may regress spontaneously.
A benign neoplasm or hamartoma composed of melanocytes.
The determination of the amount of BK virus viral load present in a sample.
A transgenic mouse at F1 generation with background strain C57BL/6 crossed with BALB/cAn, containing three copies of the human c-Ha-Ras gene introduced in tandem.
The layer located below the cerebral cortex that includes the forebrain, midbrain and hindbrain.
Any one of the three sympathetic ganglia of the cervical vertebrae.
A sequence of letters, numbers, or other characters that uniquely identifies a clinical trial within a clinical trial registry.
The minimum amount of time required to meet the criteria for a confirmed response to treatment.
The determination of the amount of cytomegalovirus viral load present in a sample.
The date on which subsequently collected data will not be considered as part of the analysis.
A textual description of the data cutoff date.
A unit of measure of the concentration of deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) copies per unit of volume equal to one milliliter.

label.value: Eosinophils to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of eosinophils compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.
The determination of the amount of Epstein-Barr virus viral load present in a sample.

Studies that provide a means for obtaining an experimental drug or device for patients who are not adequately treated by existing therapy, who do not meet the eligibility criteria for enrollment, or who are otherwise unable to participate in another clinical study. Expanded Access studies include individual-patient IND, treatment IND, compassionate use, emergency use or continued access.
A benign epithelial neoplasm of the pituitary gland.
Exploratory measures that are used to evaluate and/or form hypotheses about the intervention outcome(s).
The determination of the amount of factor IX present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of factor V present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of factor X present in a sample.
The determination of the amount of triglyceride aggregates present in a sample.
Studies that are conducted to assess the effect of food on the rate and extent of absorption of a drug, either compared to a fasted state or to a reference drug.
The determination of the amount of free kappa light chain present in a sample.

label.value: Free Kappa Light Chain to Free Lambda Light Chain Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of free kappa light chain compared to free lambda light chain present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.
